  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">BioSand Water Filters</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The objective of the Biosand Filter (BSF) Program is to provide safe clean drinking water to families affected by the earthquake and cholera epidemic.  It is expected impact is the reduction of risk to and incidences of water borne diseases (such as cholera) among the local population.  The Biosand filter is a water filtration system that removes pathogens and suspended solids, found in ground and surface water sources, through a combination of biological and physical processes. Used correctly BSFs can remove up to: 98.5% of Bacteria, 99% of Viruses, 99.9% of Protozoa, and 100% of worms (Helminths) from contaminated water.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The program will focus on three types of families (1) Households in communities dependent on river water; (2) Households in communities that have recurring cases of cholera; (3) Populations with access to water sources (such as wells with pumps) that are in danger of contamination.</narrative>
  </description>
